node.text: While photographing Rockefeller Center during the holidays I had the good fortune to be shooting from the original private balcony of Bernard Gimbel, one of the founders of Saks Fifth Avenue.  It was incredible to observe the holiday shoppers, ice skaters and the beautiful Christmas tree from such a unique vantage point.  Wishing everyone happy holidays!#DaytoNight #Taschen #NYC #holidays #christmastree #iceskating

New York City and the holiday season have become synonymous with one another.  There are so many timeless holiday traditions associated with the Big Apple and none more iconic than the Rockefeller Center Christmas Tree.  I felt so fortunate to capture this historic tree that has brought joy to so many people in this detail from my Rockefeller Center Day to Night photograph.  Wishing everyone a happy and joyous holiday season! #DaytoNight #Rockefeller Center #NYC #iceskating #ChristmasTree #lexarmemory

This photograph is from my Day to Night shoot at the Blue Lagoon in Grindivak Iceland.  One of my favorite aspects of shooting Day to Night is being able to capture multiple stories in one image.  I was especially drawn to the man in the lagoon throwing his arms up in the air in celebration. #DaytoNight #Iceland #BlueLagoon #Grindavik #lexarmemory

I took this photograph on an extraordinarily windy afternoon at the base of the Valahnukur Mountain in Iceland.  The sun began peering out from behind the clouds just at sunset, creating a dramatic contrast with the color of the water. The seascape instantly reminded me of some of the wonderful nautical paintings from the turn of the century. #DaytoNight #Iceland #Grindavik #Valahnukur #lexarmemory

Geothermal pipelines create a graphic contrast between the snow covered hills that are part of the surrounding landscape of the Blue Lagoon.  Geothermal energy meets 81% of Iceland’s energy requirements for electricity, heat & transportation.#DaytoNight #Grindavik #Blue Lagoon #Iceland #spa

On a recent trip to Churchill, Manitoba I was awed by the otherworldly beauty of the Hudson Bay. The frozen ice creates a startling contrast between the setting sun and barren landscape.
#DaytoNight #Churchill #Canada #arctic #lexarmemory

It’s amazing what you’ll find when you take the time to look.  While photographing polar bears in the arctic I was fortunate to notice this abandoned weather outpost.  I love the painting which was done by the artist @robotkin along with the graffiti that has been added over time... and the moment I began shooting a bird flew into my frame.  #Churchull #Canada #art #DaytoNight #lexarmemory #birds #arctic #fujigfx100

I never expected to see a mirage in the arctic, but while I was photographing I looked off into the distance and saw what looked like two gigantic blocks of ice floating in mid air.  Known as “Fata Morgana” it’s a rare mirage resulting from temperature differences in the bottom few meters just above the ice or sea surface.  I felt fortunate to see this phenomena while shooting in the Canadian Arctic. 
#DayToNight #lexarmemory##Churchill #Canada #mirage

Just recently returned from a new Day to Night shoot, on assignment for NGS in Churchill, Manitoba, photographing polar bears.  I witnessed an extraordinary full moonrise and moonset.  I’ve never seen this type of distortion in a moonset, where the shape of the moon distorted so that it took on the shape of a hot-air balloon, or a mushroom cloud.  This is called an Omega Moon Sun. Stay tuned for more images from this amazing trip. 
#DayToNight #lexarmemory #Churchill # Canada #moonrise #moonset

Because of the recent flooding, the Italian government has issued a call for donations, and if you are interested in helping out, you can visit:  https://www.comune.venezia.it/en/content/exceptional-high-tide-appeal-donations-italy-and-abroad  My thoughts and prayers go out to all the people in Venice. 
#DayToNight @BryceWolkowitz @Taschen @lexarmemory @atrbute #lexarmemory #Italy #SanMarco #Venice #Flooding #PeopleWatching

The city of Venice, Italy is one of my very favorite places to shoot. Unfortunately, the city has recently seen record-high flooding. Tide waters reached over 6 feet, something not seen since 1965. This Day to Night image of San Marco was photographed in 2016. The Italian government has issued a call for donations, and if you are interested in helping out, you can visit:  https://www.comune.venezia.it/en/content/exceptional-high-tide-appeal-donations-italy-and-abroad  My thoughts and prayers go out to all the people in Venice.
